summary: I hope I'm going to have so many scenes between Sansa and Daenerys! I'm curious to discover the dynamics of their relationship....
body:
I hope I’m going to have so many scenes between Sansa and Daenerys! I’m curious to discover the dynamics of their relationship.

If they manage to get along with each other, they could have the chance to develop a beautiful friendship since they share so much in common. They can relate to each other on a personal level. They might have opposite personalities, but to be honest they went through countless traumas and abuses so a genuine and sincere friendship would be something lovely to portray among them. I’d love Sansa to find a friend in Daenerys and Daenerys to find a friend in Sansa.

I’m not certain if this is something that will actually happen in Game of Thrones’s last season, but I hope so.

summary: Do you think that authors secretly write really good fan fic of their own works? Your favorite fic of some show book or movie is...
body:
Do you think that authors secretly write really good fan fic of their own works? Your favorite fic of some show book or movie is written by the creator getting their manic energy out at three am and posting it.

Like Stephanie Meyer is sitting there on her third Edward/Carlisle lemon shame fic wondering if she could change names and sell it. It worked for that other bitch.

George R.R. Martin hasn’t finished his books because he’s writing an AU where Jon and Dany are 1920’s steampunk detectives.

J.K Rowling of course has been writing fanfic of her own works since the final HP book.

title: [spoilers] What's Pycell's end game?
body:
So rewatching the DVDs for the millionth time and it really annoys me how Pycell acts all feeble and not very mobile. Yet in season 7 (I believe) he’s with a whore and kicks her out without paying and he gets up and wiggles about and is perfectly fine for an old guy. Then gets dressed exhales and hunches his back and acts weak and frail again. What is the point of this? Who cares if he’s mobile and can move around like a normal elderly man, why fake it. If it makes sense in the books or is mentioned I wouldn’t know because sadly I haven’t read them. My husband believes he does this so he’s not seen at a threat, but I don’t agree… He’s not a fighter, he’s known for being smart (I would hope) and knowledgeable as he is the doctor of thoes days.



Source: http://bit.ly/2RwFw0J
